    <updated>2026-01-05T13:57:06.344390+00:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Mend Release Bot</name>
    </author>
    <content type="html">&lt;p&gt;Unified Agent 25.11.1-223 | &lt;a class="external-link" href="https://github.com/renovatebot/renovate/releases/tag/41.173.1" rel="nofollow" shape="rect"&gt;&lt;u&gt;Renovate 41.173.1&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/a&gt; | Remediate 25.10.1 | Pre-Scan Builder (PSB) 25.8.1&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New Features and Updates&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;The following languages and package managers are now officially &lt;a data-linked-resource-id="3149365249" data-linked-resource-type="page" data-linked-resource-version="39" href="https://docs.mend.io/legacy-sca/latest/unified-agent-support-matrix"&gt;&lt;u&gt;supported&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Node.js 24.x (language)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;npm 11.x (package manager)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Gradle 9.x (package manager)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a data-linked-resource-id="3899883538" data-linked-resource-type="page" data-linked-resource-version="9" href="https://docs.mend.io/integrations/latest/configure-sca-reachability-for-gitlab"&gt;SCA Reachability&lt;/a&gt; now supports zero day configuration. When enabled, the integration will trigger a reachability scan when a new vulnerability is introduced to a dependency that is included in the users codebase.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resolved Issues&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;(SAST)&lt;/strong&gt; Fixed an issue where SAST scans on pull requests targeting an empty main branch produced misleading results and incorrectly reported a successful scan status.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://docs.mend.io/integrations/latest/mend-for-gitlab-release-notes"/>
    <published>2025-11-30T00:00:00+00:00</published>
  </entry>
