      <name>Mend Release Bot</name>
    </author>
    <content type="html">&lt;p local-id="cb0f785a-987a-425c-b72f-69516636b954"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Resolved Issues&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul local-id="81a4520a-7d82-4501-b860-672a46bc2199"&gt;&lt;li local-id="1609383d-58f0-4108-b7ee-cd912a750c7e"&gt;&lt;p local-id="28c4ac07-b5d1-4357-bfbc-1ba076ab506a"&gt;The Mend Developer Platform now supports a &lt;a data-linked-resource-id="4039442434" data-linked-resource-type="page" data-linked-resource-version="3" href="https://docs.mend.io/integrations/latest/suppress-findings-from-your-bbc-repository"&gt;suppression approval workflow for Bitbucket repositories&lt;/a&gt;. Developers can request suppressions directly from their workflows, while security managers retain control by approving or rejecting them. This ensures governance over security exceptions without slowing down development.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li local-id="8ee7c0bb-f42e-4453-a56a-9730e5df03d1"&gt;&lt;p local-id="0626f00a-936f-4e7f-a551-f85e7a73bf43"&gt;Improved handling of double unwrapping in Rust analysis.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li local-id="0fe8ee89-8432-4624-a942-b23e4020889b"&gt;&lt;p local-id="e6f1baef-1b76-4516-9658-245d9e48df9b"&gt;Updated Mend CLI code scan dependencies for improved security.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</content>
